{"id":"summaries/2025-04-23-screenshot-2025-04-23-at-9-41-21-am-93084ac1","title":"CS 461 — Ubuntu i386 libreadline fix for `access` binary","type":"summaries","html":"<p>Instructor follow-up screenshot for <a href=\"#\" class=\"mind-link\" data-node-id=\"entities/cs-461\">cs 461</a> Homework 2: enable i386 architecture, install <code>libreadline-dev:i386</code>, and symlink <code>libreadline.so.8.0 → libreadline.so.6</code> so the <code>access</code> binary runs on the Ubuntu VM — staging the <a href=\"#\" class=\"mind-link\" data-node-id=\"concepts/malware-analysis-lab\">malware analysis lab</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#\" class=\"mind-link\" data-node-id=\"entities/cs-461\">cs 461</a> · <a href=\"#\" class=\"mind-link\" data-node-id=\"concepts/cs-coursework\">cs coursework</a> · <a href=\"#\" class=\"mind-link\" data-node-id=\"concepts/malware-analysis-lab\">malware analysis lab</a> · <a href=\"#\" class=\"mind-link\" data-node-id=\"entities/osu\">osu</a></p>\n","related":[{"id":"entities/cs-461","label":"CS 461 (OSU Software Engineering capstone)"},{"id":"concepts/cs-coursework","label":"CS Coursework"},{"id":"concepts/malware-analysis-lab","label":"Malware Analysis Lab"},{"id":"entities/osu","label":"Oregon State University (OSU)"}]}
